
[1]fervency

   FERV'ENCY, n. [See fervent.]

   1. Heat of mind; ardor; eagerness.

   2. Pious ardor; animated zeal; warmth of devotion.

   When you pray, let it be with attention, with fervency, and with
   perseverance.
